videos.headline: Pathirana to Shepherd, out Bowled!! You miss, I hit! Romario can't do it with the floodlights beaming down on him in a pressure chase. He was lethal against DC, but this time plays the wrong line to this full, stump lined delivery. Pathirana strikes timber and that's the game titling back in favour of CSK. Shepherd b Pathirana 1(2)

Mustafizur to Tim David, out Caught by Ravindra!! 6,6 and OUT!! Another pace off delivery, this was a bit wider outside off. David tries to smoke it down the ground again but off the bottom end this time. Holes out to long-off. Mustafizur wins the battle, gets rid of dangerous Dave! Tim David c Ravindra b Mustafizur 13(5) [6s-2]

Tushar Deshpande to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Jadeja!! Jeez, you want the ground to swallow you whole if you are Hardik Pandya at this moment. Not often that a home wicket gets welcomed with cheers, and MS Dhoni isn't even the next player to walk out on this occasion. A short pitched delivery onto the body, Pandya takes it on with the pull but holes out to deep mid-wicket. Never got going today, timing all off for the MI skipper. Clever tactics from CSK, using Deshpande with the longer leg side boundary. Knew MI would come hard at them this over. Hardik Pandya c Jadeja b Tushar Deshpande 2(6)

Pathirana to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Mustafizur!! Big blow!! The man who scored a quickfire fifty on this same pitch last game is out without scoring today. Short of length delivery outside off, SKY tries to play an upper cut but hits it flat towards the third-man fielder. A superb piece of fielding, moves a bit to his left and reverse cups the catch with a bit of a backtrack. Realises he was losing his balance, throws the ball up and goes over the ropes, and then balances back to complete the catch. Rahman was always aware of his boundary there, Pathirana strikes again. Suryakumar Yadav c Mustafizur b Pathirana 0(2)

Pathirana to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Thakur!! First ball wicket!! A length ball onto the pads, Kishan tries to flick it away but hits it straight to Shardul to mid-wicket. Just what CSK would have wanted. For all their experience, their youngest bowler in the roster has given them the wicket. Ishan Kishan c Thakur b Pathirana 23(15) [4s-3 6s-1]

Hardik Pandya to Mitchell, out Caught by Nabi!! Hardik Pandya gets Mitchell, probably a blessing in disguise as Mitchell was struggling out there. A full toss by Hardik Pandya and Mitchell lofts it straight to Nabi at long-on. A regulation catch taken.. Mitchell c Nabi b Hardik Pandya 17(14) [4s-1]

Hardik Pandya to Gaikwad, out Caught by Nabi!! Skipper Pandya strikes. Gives the much needed breakthrough. Goes full and slightly slow outside off, Gaikwad looks to take him on. Goes for the aerial route, but doesn't middle it. Nabi from long-on charges in and completes a fine running catch. Gaikwad walks back after playing his best knock of this season. Slowly but surely getting back into his groove. Gaikwad c Nabi b Hardik Pandya 69(40) [4s-5 6s-5]

Shreyas Gopal to Ravindra, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Top call from Ishan Kishan! He was confident with the appeal and review. Shreyas Gopal surprised to see there was edge on the replay. Googly short and angling away, Ravindra goes back to cut, gets the toe-end of the bat and it's a good take by Ishan Kishan. MI get their second and pressure on CSK now. Ravindra c Ishan Kishan b Shreyas Gopal 21(16) [4s-2 6s-1]

Gerald Coetzee to Rahane, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! And there's the early wicket. The move to send Jinks up the order doesn't work. Short of a length delivery on the off stump, this one kicks up a bit, Rahane looks to pull on the rise, ball hits him high on the bat and it's total mishit for a dolly at mid-on. MI are off the mark early. Rahane c Hardik Pandya b Gerald Coetzee 5(8) [4s-1]
